data.title: Andrei Kovalev's Midlibrary
data.meta_description: (Pt. 1 of 4) In-depth look at Midjourney AI's newest model, V6: Main features + New functionality + Raw Mode (--style raw) + Comparison with V5.2

Quick Facts About V6

1

The current V6 is an Alpha test; thus, things may change.

2

V6 is more accurate in following a prompt (and is better with longer prompts).

3

The new model is more coherent.

4

It has improved image-prompting capabilities.

5

There are two new upscalers, with Subtle and Creative modes (both increase resolution by 2Ã).

6

There is an âunopinionatedâ --style raw mode (similar to V5.2).

7

You can add text to your images now!

8

Updated: the Pan, Zoom, Vary (Region) work now (and the in-depth guide on those is coming soon!), while /tune, andÂ the newÂ V6Â /describe aren't available. But they are announced toÂ arrive in the nearest weeks.

But apart from these linesâwhat is V6?

Hyperrealism

Every new version of Midjourney comes with a boost in photorealism, and V6 is no exception. In fact, the keyword that defines the new model best is Hyperrealism.

Detail Insanity

Shifted Composition

Although, at times, V6's shifts in composition might seem unrequested and unjustified, it is encouraging to see that Midjourney experiments with unconventional compositions, and expanded the overall variability of the output. Speaking of whichâ¦

And on the topic of artistic stylesâ¦

Artistic Styles In Midjourney V6

Style modifiers, or simply styles, are the names or titles you can reference in your prompts to summon a specific visual flair, technique, genre, subject, or context for your image.

Text!

Here are a few important things to remember when working with text in Midjourney V6:

Put your text in âquotations.â

Leveraging --stylize values (lower might be better), and switching to --style raw can improve the result noticeably.

Expectedly, shorter words work better. However, with enough persistence you can make Midjourney produce longer words and even whole phrases.

Adding words like text, letters, etc. to your prompt may improve the outcome.

Sometimes, you might want to double the presence of your target text in a prompt by repeating it twice in different parts of the prompt.

To demonstrate how these reccomendations applyâa few more live examples:

V6 Raw Mode

Raw is an alternativeââunopinionatedââmodel of Midjourney, existing for both, V6 and V5.2. It activates if you add --style raw to your prompt, and creates an image with âless automatic beautification applied, which can result in a more accurate match when prompting for specific styles.â

â

In this chapter, the Neat Magic Toggle switches between the Default V6 and RawÂ Mode samples!

The Raw model is more literal, and thus less âcreative.â It also tends to lean more towards existing titles when the prompt is ambiguous, i.e., offers multiple interpretations. Like in cases with destiny (also a game), perfect circle (also a music band), and David (also a statue (-â¿â¦)).

In conclusion, the --style raw parameter in Midjourney is an effective tool for diversifying results, strengthening styles that imply photorealism, or pushing the AI towards a more literal interpretation of your prompt.

In Part 2 of this exploration we will learn to talk to the new Midjourney, see what prompting strategies work best, and how complex our prompts can get. We will also test the new Image Prompting capabilities, observe how Image Weight affects the outcome, and how Blending works in V6. Continue readingÂ â
